 interest and activation of a purpose-built payload. The system consists of a vehicle, a payload, and a support system. The Dragonfish LUUV is the result of a Defense Innovation Unit (DIU) Commercial Solutions
 Opening (CSO) that assessed commercially available LUUVs. Dragonfish provides the ability to have a dispersed, long range, persistent underwater sensing and payload delivery platform to use in a contested
 environment. The platform will be large diameter, scalable, low-cost autonomous unmanned system with persistent reach and payload capacity to conduct desired mission sets.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                     Date: April 2026
