INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1810_L029$$, 2027, $$The Operating Forces Industrial Plant Equipment (IPE) budget provides funding for capital equipment procurement in support of naval shipyards and Fleet I-level maintenance activities. These investments
 deliver modern, innovative equipment essential for maintaining submarines, aircraft carriers, and surface ships; and reducing dependence on outdated IPE, weight handling systems, and nuclear support
 infrastructure. By modernizing equipment infrastructure, these procurements enhance maintenance productivity and throughput, reduce costly rework, and help maintain cost and schedule performance across
 submarine, aircraft carrier, and surface ship availabilities.

 The Capital Investment Program (CIP), a component of the Shipyard Infrastructure Optimization Program (SIOP), supports capital equipment modernization efforts at the four public naval shipyards and their
 detachments. This includes support for Virginia-Class repairs at Norfolk Naval Shipyard (NNSY), Portsmouth Naval Shipyard (PNSY), Puget Sound Naval Shipyard (PSNS & IMF), and Pearl Harbor Naval
 Shipyard (PHNSY & IMF). CIP includes providing equipment and machinery to increase the capacity of the Navy shipyards to maintain Virgina-class submarines and Ford-class carriers. Additionally, the Fleet
 Maintenance Investment Program (FMIP) funds capital equipment replacement and modernization at the U.S. Navy's regional maintenance centers and their detachments.

 Cost Code KN443 supports the Enterprise Remote Monitoring (eRM) system. eRM is the Navy's Condition Based Maintenance Plus (CBM+) Program of Record supporting Distance Support, Sea Power 21,
 Ship Maintenance (SHIPMAIN), CBM and CBM + initiatives. It is a Commercial Off-The-Shelf (COTS) based system that reduces Total Ownership Costs (TOC), maintenance and operating costs of monitored
 equipment by ensuring maintenance is accomplished based upon evidence of need.

 Condition Based Maintenance Plus (CBM+) is a maintenance optimization program that can generate significant benefits through maintenance program resets, maintenance effectiveness reviews, and active
 reliability centered maintenance (RCM) strategies at the program level. Employed as an enduring cross-life-cycle maintenance strategy, the program offers a technical solution to reduce maintenance burdens,
 increase operational availability and mission reliability of monitored systems, assists with identifying enterprise-wide cost avoidance, and will reduce overall life cycle costs.

 The Integrated Condition Assessment System (ICAS) hardware and software aboard Surface Fleet hulls (FY25 and prior Cost Codes KN800 and KN900) transitioned into the FY26 and out eRM program cited
 above.

 The FY 2026 spend plan amount for Other Procurement, Navy includes $394,998 thousand of discretionary and $390,600 thousand of mandatory (reconciliation) for a total of $785,598.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                     Date: April 2026
