INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1810_L032$$, 2027, $$The Surface Warfare (SUW) Mission Package (MP) provides Littoral Combat Ships (LCS) with increased firepower and offensive/defensive capabilities against large numbers of small manned and unmanned
 threats including fast attack craft, fast inshore attack craft, and aircraft, giving LCS the ability to protect the sea lanes and move a force quickly through a choke point or other strategic waterway.

 The SUW MP is composed of the following modules: Surface-to-Surface Missile Module (SSMM), Gun Mission Module (GMM), Maritime Security Module (MSM), and an Aviation Module. The SSMM provides
 offensive firepower to engage enemy threats at close range. A recent capability upgrade allows the SSMM to counter aircraft like drones, extending defense in addition to fast attack and fast inshore attack craft.
 The SSMM is comprised 24 Longbow Hellfire Missiles, 12 MK210 Launchers, and supporting hardware. The GMM augments the ship's 57mm gun with two high-velocity 30mm cannons. The MSM supports the
 embarkation of Visit, Board, Search, and Seizure (VBSS) teams. The Aviation Module incorporates various unmanned aircraft for surveillance. The GMM, MSM, and initial Aviation Module (with the MH-60R/S)
 achieved Initial Operational Capability (IOC) in FY 2014. The SSMM achieved IOC in FY 2019.

 For surveillance, the package aviation component has evolved. Initially, the package was first upgraded with the MQ-8B Fire Scout, a vertical take-off unmanned aerial vehicle (VTUAV) used for finding and
 identifying surface contacts. In FY24, because of the MQ-8B sunset, the Fleet invested in a contractor owned/contractor operated Aerosonde. The MK 4.7 Aerosonde, a fixed-wing unmanned aircraft that
 provides long-endurance Intelligence, Surveillance, and Reconnaissance (ISR) and is proven reliable for both land and sea operations. In FY26, the ScanEagle unmanned aircraft was added as a compatible
 asset, allowing it to be interchanged with the Aerosonde based on mission requirements.

 The inventory objective of ten deployable SUW MP has been delivered to the Fleet. Fleet requirements for SSMM has been met with five (5) production assets. A SUW MP is considered deployable and capable
 of meeting its mission requirements on an LCS only when it includes the full complement of Common Mission Modules Equipment (Line Item Number 1600) and the mission systems composing the LCS SUW
 Mission Module (Line Item Number 1603).

 [P40A / SU001 - GUN MODULE]: The Gun Mission Module (GMM) comprises two high velocity 30mm cannons to augment the ship's 57mm gun, and embarked support aircraft (MH-60R/S helicopter with Hellfire
 missile) for the detection, identification, and classification of surface contacts.

 [P40A / Gun Module Modernization/Technology Refresh]: Procures modernized Gun Module Remote Control System (GMRCS) and Gun User Interface Device (GUID), each contain computational equipment
 (including critical MAGIC-1s and Maintenance Station laptops) that are end-of-life and can no longer be procured. The rugged small form factor MAGIC1 display computer combines state-of-the-art CPU
 technology with the latest graphics processing units (GPUs) to deliver unprecedented levels of performance for GMM video and non-video applications.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                     Date: April 2026
