INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1810_L043$$, 2026, $$The Surface Ship Torpedo Defense (SSTD) program provides a layered torpedo defense to protect surface ships against current and future threats. Sustains the in-service system AN/SLQ-25A/C (NIXIE)
 countermeasure. Modernizes NIXIE to the AN/SLQ-25E variant with a technical and obsolescence refresh that also provides the baseline.

 The AN/SLQ-25 (NIXIE) is the Navy's primary SSTD system, providing towed persistent torpedo countermeasure. NIXIE currently protects all classes of surface ships. FY 2027 funding restores the AN/SLQ-25
 programs yearly budget to support engineering, procures AN/SLQ-25E Backfit systems for the fleet, and support installs. This also funds obsolescence and technical issues discovered during the AN/SLQ-25E
 system certification and first article testing as an engineering change.

 WL106 AN/SLQ-25 ENGINEERING CHANGES (ECs): Funding under this cost code provides support of three major efforts: (1) Engineering Changes for AN/SLQ-25 System that includes investigation and
 resolution of Trouble Reports (TRs), including those resulting from service-identified issues resulting in operational downtime. (2) Continuation of software modernization and system integration. (3) Continuation
 of AN/ SLQ-25C/E system support for Obsolescence, Diminishing Manufacturing Sources and Material Shortages (DMSMS) and safety improvements.

 WL830 PRODUCTION ENGINEERING-IN-HOUSE: Funding under this cost code provides specification preparation and validation, production planning, contract deliverable monitoring, prime contractor
 monitoring for cost, schedule, and performance and Integrated Logistics Support (ILS) planning, review and evaluation of obsolescence issues, and coordination of government furnished information (GFI) and
 government furnished equipment (GFE).

 WL840 QUALITY ASSURANCE: Funding under this cost code provides for quality assurance efforts including conducting quality assurance reviews of the contractor and subcontractors, documentation indicating
 contractor conformity to product performance requirements, and review of objective quality evidence.

 WL860 ACCEPTANCE TEST & ENGINEERING: Funding under this cost code provides for production acceptance of contractor hardware. Acceptance testing includes government acceptance testing and
 Environmental Qualification Testing (EQT) in support of the AN/SLQ-25 modernization with operationally trained subject matter experts and software support engineers.

 WL900 CONSULTING SERVICES: Funding under this cost code provides for contractor support to the program office for production monitoring, installation planning and coordination support.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                     Date: April 2026
