INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1810_L034$$, 2026, $$Lionfish and Viperfish are the next generation UUVs that will replace the MK18 Mod 1 and Mod 2 UUVs currently in the fleet. They are the Navy's first cybersecure UUVs, which support mine countermeasures
 (MCM), Intelligence Preparation of the Operational Environment (IPOE), Subsea and Seabed Warfare (SSW), Naval Special Warfare (NSW) Maritime Homeland Defense (MHLD) and combat salvage. Both
 provide a critical Detect-to-Engage capability to Expeditionary Mine counter measures (ExMCM) forces, organized into 18 ExMCM companies across the Navy. These UUVs can be used in very shallow to deep
 waters to clear sea mines and enable fleet movement and maneuver through chokepoints and key water space, enable logistics at sea and between sea and shore in a contested environment, and to enable
 movement of Marines from ship to shore to seize and hold key terrain in support of Expeditionary Advanced Base Operations.

 P5 / 5N300 Lionfish is a Small Unmanned Undersea Vehicle (SUUV) that replaces the legacy MK 18 Mod 1, utilizes advanced sensors and autonomy, and can be launched and recovered from small boats and
 craft, surface ships, vessels of opportunity, submarines, piers and shorelines, and various platforms. Viperfish, the deep water variant of Lionfish, replaces legacy MK 18 Mod 2 UUVs, and leverages recent
 innovation and technical advances to enable it to be delivered in a Small UUV form factor using Lionfish as a baseline as an ECP with enhanced depth performance and mission capability.

 P5 / 5N001 KNIFEFISH (SMCM UUV w/LFBB)]: The Knifefish Surface Mine Countermeasure Unmanned Undersea Vehicle (SMCM UUV) program procures Unmanned Undersea Vehicles to support clandestine
 mine detection capability against volume and bottom mines including buried mine detection. The Knifefish system is composed of two UUVs, batteries, launch and handling system, and other support equipment.

 P5 / 5N100 TETRA: TETRA is a Remotely Operated Vehicle (ROV) with the capacity for multiple mission payloads as a key enabler to Subsea and Seabed Warfare (SSW) as identified in the SSW Initial
 Capabilities Document
 (ICD). A single TETRA system is comprised of 2 ROVs equipped with mission-dependent payload(s) and Ancillary Equipment

 The FY 2026 spend plan for Small and Medium Unmanned Undersea Vehicles (UUVs) program includes $7,000 thousand of discretionary funding and $345,086 thousand of mandatory funding for a total of
 $352,086 thousand. The mandatory funds unmanned underwater vehicle production.

 [P5 / 5N001 KNIFEFISH (SMCM UUV w/LFBB)]: The Knifefish Surface Mine Countermeasure Unmanned Undersea Vehicle (SMCM UUV) program procures Unmanned Undersea Vehicles to support
 clandestine mine detection capability against volume and bottom mines including buried mine detection. The Knifefish system is composed of two UUVs, batteries, launch and handling system, and other support
 equipment.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                     Date: April 2026
