INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1810_L037$$, 2026, $$Modernized LSD 41/49 Class ships transport and launch amphibious craft and vehicles with their crews and embarked personnel in amphibious assault operations. Supporting amphibious operations include
 landings via Landing Craft, Air Cushion (LCAC), conventional landing craft, and helicopters, onto hostile shores.

 [P40A / ST5IN LSD Installation / DSA / AIT]: Planned effort by the Alteration Installation Teams (AITs) and the Design Support Activity (DSA) to address ship's growing obsolescence issues and maintenance
 intensive areas via support in the Modernization Availabilities.

 [P40A / Slewing Arm Davit (SLAD) Embarkation Platform Installation]: LSD Class ships require an embarkation platform for loading and unloading of personnel during launch and recovery operations utilizing
 the new Lake Shore Inc. Slewing Arm Davit (SLAD). The upgrade is required due to limited space in the area of the 11M RIB stowage, which limits the ability of the crew to efficiently load and unload personnel,
 particularly during recovery operations.

 [P40A / Slewing Arm Davit (SLAD) Installation]: This SHIPALT replaces the Welin Lambie LUM 12A or Lakeshore Gravity Boat Davit currently installed on LSD 41/49 Class ships, with a new Slewing Arm Davit
 (SLAD) from Oldenburg Group Inc. The existing systems will be removed and the OGI SLAD will be installed in the same general location of the current systems. The new system is a SLAD design with single
 point pick up of the boats versus the two points pick up used by the existing systems.

 [P40A / Ballast Control Console (BCC)]: Provides upgrades to the existing Ballast Control Consoles (BCC) and replaces legacy BCC with a Programmable Logic Controller (PLC) based digital, networked system.
 This mission and safety critical SCD address system degradation due to obsolescence issues, extensive downtime and reduced system capability/reliability. The system is currently operating in a degraded
 capacity and requires immediate replacement.

 [P40A / Damage Control Console (DCC)]: This SCD upgrades the existing Damage Control (DC) Console and interior communication sensor monitoring (IC/SM) alarm panels within Damage Control Central
 on-board ship with a Programmable Logic Controller (PLC) based control system that will provide all current functionality and utilizes the Advanced Engineering Control System (AECS) network backbone. The
 software will leverage the LSD 47 interface for system screen layout and user interaction but will be developed using the current Platform Independent Machinery Control System (PIMCS) software architecture
 and includes the Advanced Damage Control System (ADCS) hardware and software. ADCS provides real-time, dynamic ship status and parametric information, and accepts feedback on actions taken by watch
 standers.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                     Date: April 2026
