INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1810_L038$$, 2027, $$The Undersea Special Mission Systems Program, formerly Deep Submergence Systems Program (DSSP), is responsible for the procurement, life cycle support, improvement and modernization of assigned
 platforms and programs. The Undersea Special Missions Systems Program provides for the procurement of equipment to support the establishment and maintenance of fleet capability for a number of programs
 which perform submarine rescue, escape, search, inspection, and object location and retrieval from the ocean environment. Submarine escape and rescue procurements replace obsolete, non-supportable
 equipment and subsystems through phased improvement and modernization projects. These projects may include special ship alterations, field change kits, and design corrections.

 FY2027 funding provides modernization of special mission systems, including the Navy's only Submarine Rescue System (SRS) assets. Modernization of the SRS is necessary to address known reliability and
 obsolescence issues and to sustain the system through its end-of-life period, ensuring continued operability until replacement.

 SOURCES: The sources for these acquisitions are limited. There are few private companies actively engaged in deep ocean engineering and even fewer with the specialized certifications, experience,
 knowledge, and facilities to meet the exacting requirements of submarine escape and rescue. Accordingly, sole source contracts are sometimes required; however, where possible, contracting via open
 competition is utilized.

 [P40A / HJ030 - RESCUE SUPPORT EQUIPMENT]: Intervention Systems (Remotely Operated Vehicles (ROV)/ SRS: Intervention assets (ROV) are required to support the SRS world-wide rescue capability
 mission. Intervention assets are used to clear disabled submarine's seating surfaces, attach salvage fittings, deliver emergency life support stores, and assess distressed submarines condition. The ROV is an
 unmanned system that reduces operational risk from the previous Intervention Assets that were a manned system, Atmospheric Diving System (ADS). SRS is the pressurized rescue ready system for the U.S.
 Navy. SRS was delivered in increments; the Submarine Rescue System-Rescue Capable System (SRS-RCS) completed OPEVAL in FY08, and the final component of SRS was the Submarine Rescue System-
 Submarine Decompression System (SRS-SDS) providing the Transfer Under Pressure (TUP) capability which has been delivered and completed Initial Operating Capability (IOC)/Final Operating Capability
 (FOC) in FY2019.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                     Date: April 2026
