INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1810_L061$$, 2027, $$Funding for Maritime Integrated Broadcast System (MIBS) has been realigned out of line item 2900 into line item 2361 starting in FY 2026. This is to consolidate the number of program elements (PE) and budget
 line items (BLI) to group technology projects to allow flexibility fostering innovation and efficiency. PE/BLI consolidation meets the DoD Implementation Plan from the Commission on PPBE Final Report.

 The MIBS program delivers Integrated Broadcast Service (IBS) data to operational and tactical decision makers aboard United States Navy surface ships, shore headquarters, and other joint platforms. MIBS
 provides the Navy with the capability to receive and deliver near real time, Over the Air (OTA) IBS data, enhancing the Common Operation Picture (COP) supporting operations in all warfare areas. Including
 Ballistic Missile Defense (BMD), Anti-Air Warfare (AAW), Anti-Surface Warfare (ASUW), Undersea Warfare (UW), Electronic Warfare (EW) and track location of red and blue forces to warfighters at the tactical
 edge, regardless of Emission Control (EMCON) posture. MIBS provides essential support to the Over the Horizon-Targeting (OTH-T) mission and supports closure of the kill chain in a denied environment.

 This budget will provide a technical refresh of the Joint Tactical Terminal - Maritime (JTT-M) systems. The Joint Tactical Terminal - Maritime Evolved (JTT-ME) system replaces an End of Life (EoL) JTT-
 Senior terminals and infrastructure with a modern, secure, network enabled infrastructure that allows flexibility for future radios/waveforms. This system is formally specified by Fleet Commanders as a threshold
 capability for global Maritime Command, Control and Communications in a Distributed Maritime Environment to execute current Warfighting plans and is required for National Command and Control capability.
 The MIBS program will replace the End of Life (EoL) JTT-Senior radio (JTT-M) that has been in sustainment for 20+ years.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                      Date: April 2026
