INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1810_L051$$, 2026, $$Advanced Tactical Data Link Systems (ATDLS) is the United States (US) Navy's only ship-to-ship/ship-to-aircraft tactical information solution equipping warfighters and Combatant Commanders with real-time
 battlespace data and extending the range of lethality. ATDLS is the backbone of Carrier Strike Group and AEGIS-Based Defense operations and is the key component in the fire control loop, providing critical
 track information for enabling maritime offense/defense, Joint Area Domain Command and Control (JADC2), Integrated Air and Missile Defense (IAMD), Ballistic Missile Defense (BMD), Anti-Air Warfare (AAW),
 Anti-Surface Warfare (ASuW), Electronic Warfare (EW), Advanced Offboard Electronic Warfare (AOEW), and Long Range Fires (LRF) missions. ATDLS Integration Program develops new and improved Tactical
 Data Links (TDL) networking capabilities, delivering operational and targeting support to the warfighter. ATDLS rapidly and securely connects carrier/shipboard digital combat systems to military aircraft, ground
 troops, coalition partners, and space assets with vital Situational Awareness, targeting, and sensor information. ATDLS also provides Joint Range Extension capability via Link 16 Network (Link 16) Terminals,
 Command and Control Processor (C2P), and Link Monitoring and Management Tool (LMMT).

 C2P Technology Refresh (TR) and C2P Modernization (MOD) Full Systems Ship/Shore (DR003): C2P is the only shipboard solution that enables bi-directional exchange of tactical information across multiple
 TDLs within the joint operations areas. C2P processes and exchanges Link 11, Link 16, Satellite TDL J, and Joint Range Extension Applications Protocol (JREAP) tactical data among the US, North Atlantic
 Treaty Organization (NATO), and allied nation military platforms enabling the vital joint TDL interface. Additionally, C2P provides data translation services, acts as a single interface between host combat system
 and TDL networks, and forwards tactical data between platforms operating at extended ranges. C2P enables surface platforms capability to conduct Ballistic Missile Defense BMD Launch-on-Remote/Engage-
 on-Remote and Autonomous Vehicle missions. C2P TR with C2P v3.13 software baseline enables Tactical Targeting Network Technology (TTNT), equipping warfighters with faster network speed and improved
 capacity. C2P MOD procurements seamlessly cut-in starting FY26 utilizing existing contract strategy. C2P Mod delivers Link 22 capability allowing interoperability with coalition partners; as well as enabling an
 agile DevSecOps software deployment for rapid capability and cybersecurity upgrades, enabling continuous kill chain improvements.

 Link 16 TTNT Upgrade Kits (DR012): Link 16 enhanced by TTNT serves as the military's only joint network capable of providing secure tactical data link interoperability and data sharing in contested battlespace
 environments. These upgrade kits modernize currently fielded Link 16 cabinets through two primary configurations: the Multifunctional Information Distribution System (MIDS) on-Ship (MOS) and MOS
 Modernization (MOS Mod). The Link 16 TTNT MOS-J Upgrade Kit and Link 16 TTNT MOS Mod enhance existing configurations in accordance with Joint Chiefs of Staff Joint Requirements Oversight Council
 Memorandum (JROCM) 075-17, enabling the integration and installation of MIDS Joint Tactical Radio System (MIDS JTRS) terminals within Navy shipboard environments. Key Modernization Features
 include: (1) MOS and MOS Mod cabinet modernization, enabling TTNT operations on shipboard and shore. Upgrades in MIDS-JTRS AV6, TTNT power amplifier, external GPS input, and updated controller
 interface computer. (2) Enhanced Capabilities, implementation of JROCM 097-20 and the JROC-validated MIDS JTRS Capability Production Document (CPD) dated February 10, 2011, which mandates Crypto
 Modernization (CM), Frequency Remapping (FR), Enhanced Throughput (ET), Concurrent Multi-Netting (CMN), and Current Contention Receive (CCR).$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                      Date: April 2026
