INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1810_L081$$, 2027, $$Aligned under Joint Enabling Capabilities Command (JECC), U.S. Transportation Command (USTRANSCOM) - Joint Communications Support Element (JCSE) is the only Department of War (DoW) organization
 specifically formed that provides crisis and contingency communications to meet the operational support needs of the Joint Chiefs of Staff (JCS), Combatant Commands (CC), DoW agencies and non-DoW
 agencies. The mission of JCSE is to provide rapidly deployable, en route, early entry, and scalable coalition command, control, computers, intelligence, surveillance, and reconnaissance (C4ISR) capabilities to
 CCs and other agencies as directed to facilitate rapid establishment and transitions of Joint Forces Headquarters (JFHQ), and bridge joint communications requirements. JCSE seamlessly scales C4ISR support
 for conventional or unconventional JFHQs. JCSE has a robust 24/7 reach back capability through its Global Enterprise Network and has access to a full range of DoW and commercial networks.

 The Vice Director through Director Joint Staff Memorandum (DJSM) 0148-20, directs Services to fund 1/3 share of the JCSE Modernization Program. This is essential for JCSE to maintain mission readiness
 to meet directed capabilities within Chairman's Joint Chief of Staff Instruction (CJCSI 3110.10G & 5131.10) as well as Joint Publication 6-0. The modernization program is a key component that allows JCSE
 to rapidly acquire current technology and configure it for DoW use to remain ready, relevant, and agile for crisis and contingency. JCSE's Modernization Program is based on CC and Service Components
 requirements and emerging technologies. The Services influence JCSEs spending plan through recommendations in concert with Major Defense Acquisition Program (MDAP) schedules, ensuring the Service
 investments meet Joint Service Requirements.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                      Date: April 2026
