INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1810_L089$$, 2026, $$The Identification Systems program funds procurements and Engineering Change Proposals (ECPs) to address obsolescence and fact of life changes, installations, and certifications for the following Mark XII /
 Mark XIIA systems: AN/UPX-37, AN/UPX-41, AN/UPX-45 and AN/UPX-50 Digital Interrogators (DIs), AN/APX-118 and AN/APX-123 Common Digital Transponders (CXPs), AN/UPX-29 Interrogator System
 (comprised of Interrogator Set AN/UPX-24 or AN/UPX-49, OE-120/ UPX Antenna Group, and Mark XII or Mark XIIA equipment), AN/UPX-29 Modernization (UPneXt/Common Core), AN/UPX-46 Interrogator
 System (comprised of CP-2819/UPX Processor and Mark XIIA equipment), Identification Friend or Foe (IFF) support equipment, and AN/UPX-34A Radar Track Discriminator System (RTDS).

 The Air Traffic Control Radar Beacon System, IFF, Mark XII/XIIA System (AIMS) is a Department of War directed tri-service program designed to provide a universal air traffic control radar beacon system
 compatible with the National Airspace System program. It provides a secure identification system for military use on all combatant ships, selected auxiliaries, patrol craft, and selected Coast Guard ships by
 allowing all friendly forces to identify each other and neutral forces. The Mark XII/XIIA system supports several missions such as anti-air warfare, aerial bombardment, and naval attack.

 The OE-120/UPX antenna radiates Identification Friend or Foe (IFF) encoded Radio Frequency (RF) challenge pulses into space and receives the resultant IFF encoded RF transponder replies from space.
 Current surface ship OE-120()/UPX antenna systems will receive upgrade kits to improve system R&M. The upgrade kits will use open architecture and current technology that allows for continued production
 and future growth. An Engineering Change Proposal was awarded using RDT&E (PU 0676) funds for the Original Equipment Manufacturer to deliver an Engineering Design Model for shipboard test and
 evaluation in FY 2018.

 Modernization of the DDG 1000 Zumwalt Class IFF Sensor Suite includes procurement activities, product improvements, and engineering changes for three Electronically Scanned Array (ESA) antennas, one
 UPX-42(C) Interrogator, and three RT-1912(C)/APX Transponders.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                     Date: April 2026
