INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1810_L118$$, 2026, $$The Meteorological Equipment budget line item provides new and replacement meteorological equipment for Navy and Marine Corps Air Stations, Navy ships, Marine Corps Operational Force units and other
 activities required to provide weather observations and provide safety of flight capabilities. It also provides new Intelligence Preparation of the Operational Environment (IPOE) equipment for submarines. The
 Meteorological Equipment procurement has been coordinated with other Department of War (DoW) and civilian agencies.

 [P40A / SP051 Satellite Receiver Upgrades (Space)]: Environmental Satellite Receiver Processor Systems (ESRP Ashore and ESRP Afloat) receive and process remotely sensed data in L and S frequency
 bands from several National and International Meteorology and Oceanography (METOC) Satellite families such as the Defense Meteorological Satellite Program (DMSP) Polar Satellites, the National Oceanic
 and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) Satellites, and the Geostationary Operational Environmental Satellite (GOES-R) Series. Integration of next generation polar and geostationary orbiting satellite families
 and new sensors of opportunity shall be incorporated in the hardware design and software upgrades to existing Environmental Satellite Receiver Processor Systems both afloat and ashore. The modernization of
 systems includes GOES-R, Electro-Optical/Infrared Weather Systems - Geostationary (EWS-G), and Weather System Follow-On Microwave (WSF-M) ingest of METOC data, as well as the addition of X and C
 frequency bands for current and future capabilities.

 [P40A / SP550 METOC SASC Upgrades]: Procures Government Off-The-Shelf/Commercial Off-The-Shelf hardware and associated software upgrades for the 69 fielded Automated Surface Observing Systems
 (ASOS) and the 9 fielded Supplemental Weather Radars (SWR). Both atmospheric sensing systems are essential for aviation safety, Naval Aviation operations, and resource protection. ASOS procurements
 under this project will provide system upgrades as required by the 2025 National Weather Service Interagency Agreement. SWR upgrades of End of Life components, software, and subsystems under this project
 provide System Life Extension by mitigating CYBER risk and Diminishing Manufacturing Sources and Material Shortages (DMSMS).

 [P40A / SP600 Littoral Battlespace Sensing - Unmanned Undersea Vehicles (LBS-UUV)]: Littoral Battlespace Sensing - Unmanned Undersea Vehicles (LBS-UUV) procures ocean sensor systems. The vehicles
 are a highly persistent oceanographic sensing/data collection capability (buoyancy driven Gliders that sense ocean volume parameters such as conductivity, temperature, depth, optical clarity, currents, etc.)
 in support of CNOs and Fleet Intelligence Preparation of the Operational Environment (IPOE), Undersea Warfare (USW), Antisubmarine Warfare (ASW), Mine Warfare (MIW), Naval Special Warfare (NSW),
 Subsea and Seabed Warfare (SSW) and Naval Expeditionary operations. The Gliders are controlled remotely and maintained from the Naval Oceanographic Office (NAVOCEANO), Stennis Space Center,
 Mississippi from the Glider Operations Center (GOC). Quantities represent the fleet goals of 50 gliders operational, or at-the-ready, out of a population of 150, with follow-on Gliders to continue an annual
 acquisition of 15 Gliders/yr. Recommended lifespan of 5 years has been extended 2xs over, through following the ongoing required manufacturer recommended maintenance (repairs, calibrations, and parts
 obsolescence) and RDT&E efforts managed by the PEO. These efforts systematically improved the Gliders with longer endurance and capabilities, crucial in reaching and maintaining the Fleets goal of 150
 Gliders, while also continuously improving Glider components. This leads to minimized system loss, improved battery management and diminished sensor failures.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                      Date: April 2026
